The paper deals with a streaming data model and the analysis of the singular value decomposition (SVD) of the matrix of data. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of the results to a streaming graph algorithm, which could place it in the categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
